The International Federation of Journalists has called for an investigation into the murder of Pakistani journalist Khadim Hussain Sheikh. The bureau chief of Urdu daily newspaper Khabrein and a stinger for Sindh TV, in Baluchistan was travelling to his office on a motorbike with his brother when gunmen intercepted them. Both men were shot at close range. Khadim died instantly and his brother was seriously injured. He is the third journalist killed in Pakistan this year. (Via IFJ)